\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Overall architecture of the proposed HAG-DTA model. The model consists of a hierarchical graph neural network (HGNN), a deep graph neural network (DGNN), a convolutional neural network (CNN), and an attention-based fusion module. HGNN extracts functional group-level and fragment-level molecular features through hierarchical graph pooling, DGNN captures global molecular topological features, and CNN extracts local protein sequence features. The attention block adaptively integrates these multi-source representations for drug-target affinity prediction.}}{10}{figure.caption.3}\protected@file@percent }
\providecommand*\caption@xref[2]{\@setref\relax\@undefined{#1}}
\newlabel{fig1}{{1}{10}{Overall architecture of the proposed HAG-DTA model. The model consists of a hierarchical graph neural network (HGNN), a deep graph neural network (DGNN), a convolutional neural network (CNN), and an attention-based fusion module. HGNN extracts functional group-level and fragment-level molecular features through hierarchical graph pooling, DGNN captures global molecular topological features, and CNN extracts local protein sequence features. The attention block adaptively integrates these multi-source representations for drug-target affinity prediction}{figure.caption.3}{}}
\newlabel{eq:diffpool_x}{{4}{10}{Hierarchical graph representation learning module(HGNN)}{equation.4}{}}
\newlabel{eq:diffpool_a}{{5}{10}{Hierarchical graph representation learning module(HGNN)}{equation.5}{}}
